sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Offensive tradecraft is switching away from using APIs like "CreateRemoteThread", however, this is still largely observed in the wild. This rule aims to detect suspicious processes (those we would not expect to behave in this way like word.exe or outlook.exe) creating remote threads on other processes. It is a generalistic rule, but it should have a low FP ratio due to the selected range of processes.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Bad Opsec Defaults Sacrificial Processes With Improper Arguments
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects attackers using tooling with bad opsec defaults e.g. spawning a sacrificial process to inject a capability into the process without taking into account how the process is normally run, one trivial example of this is using rundll32.exe without arguments as a sacrificial process (default in CS, now highlighted by c2lint), running WerFault without arguments (Kraken - credit am0nsec), and other examples.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Oleg Kolesnikov @securonix invrep_de, oscd.community, Florian Roth, Christian Burkard

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Rundll32 Without Any CommandLine Params
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects suspicious start of rundll32.exe without any parameters as found in CobaltStrike beacon activity

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: New Lolbin Process by Office Applications
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: This rule will monitor any office apps that spins up a new LOLBin process. This activity is pretty suspicious and should be investigated.
Detects the execution of rundll32 with a command line that doesn't contain a .dll file
Detects a specific process creation patterns as seen used by UNC2452 and provided by Microsoft as Microsoft Defender ATP queries

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: LOLBAS rundll32 without expected arguments (via cmdline)
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects use of rundll32 as a LOLBAS binary where rundll32 is passed unexpected arguments such as a .iso instead of .dll (i.e. rundll32.exe test.iso, evilexport).

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious Execution of Powershell with Base64
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Commandline to lauch powershell with a base64 payload
Code integrity failures may indicate tampered executables.
